these two types combined in L28-30 feels very weird; 

I think it makes more sense to have:
```ts
export interface NotificationCenterSuccessfulResponse {
  notifications: Notification[];
}

export interface NotificationCenterFailedResponse {
  error: string;
}

export type NotificationCenterResponse =
  | NotificationCenterSuccessfulResponse
  | NotificationCenterFailedResponse;
```

but at the same time, wouldn't failures actually throw an error instead? (i.e., status code is not 200s-300s?). In that case, rxjs/http_client actually throws and there is a rxjs way of catching that (https://www.learnrxjs.io/learn-rxjs/operators/error_handling/catch; you've already done that in effects). If my intuition is correct, you will not need the error type.

